📌 Relationship idea:
One Notaire → can have MANY Dossier_Terrain
One Dossier_Terrain → belongs to ONE Notaire

👉 This is called:

One-to-Many relationship
The # (foreign key) is ALWAYS in the CHILD table

✔️ hasMany (Parent)
has no foreign key
gives list of children
✔️ belongsTo (Child)
contains foreign key (#)
belongs to one parent
🔥 Super simple memory trick

👉 “The table that HAS the # is the CHILD”
